Thank you.

18:12.359 --> 18:13.693
(sighs)

18:13.726 --> 18:15.695
You searched the school
for her, right?

18:15.728 --> 18:17.264
Yeah, of course.

18:17.297 --> 18:19.399
Look, I think she
has Asperger's.

18:19.432 --> 18:22.269
I told the parents, and
the father got very angry,

18:22.302 --> 18:23.870
said she was normal.

18:23.903 --> 18:26.339
We brought in an interventionist
to work with her,

18:26.373 --> 18:27.874
and the father
threatened to sue.

18:27.907 --> 18:30.210
I worry about her
all the time.

18:30.243 --> 18:32.412
She has almost
no friends.

18:32.445 --> 18:34.747
Uh... she likes art.

18:34.781 --> 18:37.384
(gentle laugh)
She keeps building these--

18:37.417 --> 18:39.719
sorry-- these...

18:39.752 --> 18:41.288
structures.

18:41.321 --> 18:42.922
It's weird, huh?

18:42.955 --> 18:44.824
She's kind of
a savant.

18:44.857 --> 18:46.193
Hmm.

18:46.193 --> 18:47.727
Can I keep this?

18:47.760 --> 18:49.796
Yeah, of course.

18:50.897 --> 18:52.832
I gotta call this in.

18:57.704 --> 19:00.207
Hey, Sarge, we got an
at-risk missing child.

19:00.207 --> 19:03.210
Last seen at a bus stop at
Ardmore and Harvard around 8:00.

19:07.247 --> 19:08.848
She's got a disability.

19:08.881 --> 19:11.351
I think she may have Asperger's.

19:15.655 --> 19:17.690
SALESWOMAN:
You really can't go wrong
with the Storecraft.

19:17.724 --> 19:19.226
LYDIA:
And that's this one
here, right?

19:19.226 --> 19:20.393
We stopped carrying
some others.

19:20.427 --> 19:21.461
Lead problems,
bracket problems,

19:21.494 --> 19:23.463
mattress collapses,
you name it.

19:23.496 --> 19:25.465
Mattress collapses.
Really?

19:25.498 --> 19:28.235
I really like this
one, honey.

19:28.268 --> 19:30.403
You're a gorgeous couple.

19:30.437 --> 19:31.971
Well, thank you.

19:32.004 --> 19:33.440
When are you due?

19:33.473 --> 19:34.841
I'm not pregnant.

19:34.874 --> 19:37.244
I run six miles a day,
do I look fat to you?

19:37.277 --> 19:38.245
Sorry.

19:38.245 --> 19:39.379
Give me your credit card,

19:39.412 --> 19:40.980
we're splitting
this, honey.

19:41.013 --> 19:43.250
That's crazy-- why would
I have to split this with you?

19:43.283 --> 19:45.552
I'm going to pay you back,
it's just for right now.

19:51.258 --> 19:53.260
Thanks, sweetie.

19:53.260 --> 19:55.262
I'll need to have it
delivered.

19:58.598 --> 20:01.000
Yeah, room 617, please.

20:01.033 --> 20:03.002
You have an incisional hernia.

20:03.035 --> 20:04.871
What were you doing, sit-ups?

20:04.904 --> 20:07.240
Going for a new
personal best?

20:07.274 --> 20:08.575
Heavy weights?

20:08.608 --> 20:09.976
So what happens now?

20:10.009 --> 20:12.011
The bulge has a loop
of intestine in it.

20:12.044 --> 20:13.980
We gotta go in
and get it.

20:16.048 --> 20:17.717
How about the colostomy
takedown?

20:17.750 --> 20:18.818
Not, not yet.

20:18.851 --> 20:20.353
(phone vibrating)

20:20.387 --> 20:22.622
What about the numbness
and weakness in his leg?

20:22.655 --> 20:23.790
Totally normal.

20:23.823 --> 20:25.325
The blast wave from
the bullet

20:25.358 --> 20:27.026
caused damage to the
lumbrosacral plexus.

20:27.059 --> 20:29.529
Nerves need to heal.

20:29.562 --> 20:31.498
(vibrating continues)
Takes time.

20:38.571 --> 20:41.874
Hey, Russ, I tried you at the
hospital a couple times.

20:41.908 --> 20:44.444
Um, just want to hear
your voice,

20:44.477 --> 20:47.314
say hello, something.

20:47.347 --> 20:50.317
I went and saw Brianna,
um, today.

20:50.350 --> 20:53.320
Jimmy is getting so big.

20:53.353 --> 20:56.323
Anyway, um, give me
a call, partner.

20:56.356 --> 20:57.457
All right?

20:57.490 --> 20:59.426
I love you. Bye.

21:12.739 --> 21:15.342
Yeah, that's it.
Uh, she was last
seen at a bus stop

21:15.375 --> 21:16.743
at, uh, Ardmore and
Harvard around 8:00.

21:17.977 --> 21:19.446
I spoke to your
watch commander.

21:19.479 --> 21:20.880
You're clear from this;
you go back

21:20.913 --> 21:22.549
to handling your calls.
Thanks for your help.

21:22.582 --> 21:24.517
Good work.

21:34.961 --> 21:36.529
(phone rings)

21:36.563 --> 21:37.530
Sherman.

21:37.564 --> 21:39.432
It's, uh, Stella.

21:39.466 --> 21:41.434
Um, Stella Holmes.

21:41.468 --> 21:43.102
Hey. You all right?

21:43.135 --> 21:46.373
No, he keeps calling me
and threatening me.

21:46.406 --> 21:47.874
Where is he right now?

21:47.907 --> 21:49.409
He's at the restaurant.

21:49.442 --> 21:50.410
I can hear the kitchen
in the background.

21:50.443 --> 21:51.444
Um, it's called "Soren."

21:51.478 --> 21:53.380
It's in Silverlake.

21:53.380 --> 21:57.650
I'm sorry. I wouldn't bother you
if I wasn't so scared.

21:57.684 --> 21:59.386
It's just, it was so bad,
you know?

21:59.386 --> 22:01.954
He just, he kept ranting.

22:01.988 --> 22:03.890
Yeah, all right.
Sit tight for a minute.

22:03.923 --> 22:05.392
I'm gonna call you back, okay?

22:05.392 --> 22:06.893
Bye.

22:38.190 --> 22:39.792
MAN:
All right, people,
let's go!

22:39.826 --> 22:42.128
It's gonna be
a full house tonight!

22:42.161 --> 22:43.830
Pick up the energy!

22:43.863 --> 22:45.432
Who are you?

22:45.465 --> 22:47.066
What are you doing
in my kitchen?!

22:47.099 --> 22:49.802
Can I talk
to you outside, please?

22:49.836 --> 22:52.071
Oh, all right,
here we go.

22:52.104 --> 22:54.441
What did she say
I did this time?

22:54.474 --> 22:56.075
Tom Sorenson.

22:56.108 --> 22:59.078
The day I hired
this chick was

22:59.111 --> 23:01.180
the worst day of my life.

23:01.213 --> 23:02.582
Did you meet her?

23:02.615 --> 23:05.051
She seems great, right?

23:05.084 --> 23:07.720
At first, yeah,
she's a total doll,

23:07.754 --> 23:08.721
and then...

23:08.755 --> 23:09.956
I'm onto you.

23:09.989 --> 23:12.058
What'd you just say to me?

23:12.091 --> 23:13.726
I'm onto you.

23:15.462 --> 23:18.765
Arrested for stalking
and trespass in 2008.

23:18.798 --> 23:19.966
Come on, man.

23:19.999 --> 23:21.568
Battery, 2006.

23:21.601 --> 23:23.035
Case dismissed.
D.A. reject.

23:23.069 --> 23:24.571
Date rape, 2006.

23:24.604 --> 23:25.572
No charges filed.

23:25.605 --> 23:26.939
Is that how you do it?

23:26.973 --> 23:28.841
Do you scare 'em into
dropping the charges?

23:32.545 --> 23:35.214
This is no longer
a consensual encounter.

23:35.247 --> 23:38.217
Good-bye.

23:38.250 --> 23:39.952
Where'd you learn
that term?

23:39.986 --> 23:43.523
From the lawyers you hire
after you beat up women?

23:43.556 --> 23:46.526
She was a lousy cook,
and I fired her, okay?

23:46.559 --> 23:49.128
Now you tell her
to stop stalking me!

23:52.064 --> 23:55.101
You touch her...
I'm coming after you.

23:59.572 --> 24:01.674
Have a nice day.

24:01.708 --> 24:04.544
Stay for dinner!

24:04.577 --> 24:05.778
Let's go, people!

24:05.812 --> 24:06.746
Keep it up!

24:09.248 --> 24:11.117
(siren wails briefly,
helicopter flies over)

24:21.060 --> 24:24.163
LYDIA:
Why wasn't he
wearing a helmet?

24:24.196 --> 24:25.965
I told him not to.

24:25.998 --> 24:27.534
You what?

24:27.567 --> 24:28.835
We were filming it.

24:28.868 --> 24:31.538
It's like a Jackass
kind of thing.

24:31.571 --> 24:33.740
Okay.

24:33.773 --> 24:35.608
Famous people
never wear helmets.

24:35.642 --> 24:38.044
You gotta be able
to see their face.

24:38.077 --> 24:40.613
Otherwise,
it could be anyone.

24:40.647 --> 24:41.914
Let me get this
straight.

24:41.948 --> 24:44.884
The end of the stunt
going at 35 miles an hour,

24:44.917 --> 24:48.054
jumping into an
empty swimming pool,

24:48.087 --> 24:49.856
and you told him
not to wear a helmet?

24:49.889 --> 24:52.124
We were gonna put it
on YouTube, man.

24:52.158 --> 24:53.626
It was gonna be radical.

24:53.660 --> 24:55.695
(forced laugh)
I bet.

24:57.196 --> 24:58.297
You know,
it's manslaughter.

24:58.330 --> 24:59.566
He acted recklessly.

24:59.566 --> 25:01.000
Yes, that's exactly why

25:01.033 --> 25:02.635
they're not gonna file
for manslaughter.

25:02.669 --> 25:04.003
So you're saying it's
reckless endangerment?

25:04.036 --> 25:06.172
I'm saying the parents
will never let him say

25:06.205 --> 25:07.874
that he made him
take the helmet off.

25:10.710 --> 25:12.078
It's your call.

25:12.111 --> 25:15.715
These kids aren't
going anywhere.

25:15.748 --> 25:17.950
We'll run it by the DA.

25:17.984 --> 25:19.752
They've got to live
with this

25:19.786 --> 25:21.688
for the rest
of their lives.

25:23.756 --> 25:25.257
(Lydia sighs)

25:27.760 --> 25:29.696
What are you
looking at, pig?

25:35.868 --> 25:37.169
Want to grab
a quick bite?

25:37.203 --> 25:39.639
No, I'm gonna run
by the hospital

25:39.672 --> 25:41.674
and say hi to Russ.

25:43.976 --> 25:46.713
I'lll drop you off
at the station, all right?

25:46.746 --> 25:48.615
You think that's a good idea,

25:48.648 --> 25:50.617
you going to see him
all the time?

25:50.650 --> 25:52.151
What?

25:52.184 --> 25:54.621
I mean, he's lying
in a hospital bed,

25:54.621 --> 25:56.656
and you're still
calling him "partner."

25:56.689 --> 25:58.324
That can't make him feel good.

25:58.357 --> 26:01.227
You should let him go
a little bit.

26:01.260 --> 26:03.062
You're telling me
how to treat this man

26:03.095 --> 26:05.164
you've never even
met before?

26:05.197 --> 26:06.666
You're kidding me, right?

26:06.699 --> 26:09.636
Look, you don't know
anything about us.

26:09.636 --> 26:11.938
You don't know anything
about our bond.

26:11.971 --> 26:14.674
I'm just trying
to give him hope

26:14.707 --> 26:17.076
and let him know
I'm still there for him.

26:17.109 --> 26:18.711
I'm sorry.

26:18.745 --> 26:22.014
I'm just saying calling him
"partner" all the time

26:22.048 --> 26:23.816
and trying to keep him
up-to-date with cases,

26:23.850 --> 26:26.719
I just think,
I don't know...

26:26.753 --> 26:30.757
Look, just stay out of it,
all right?! It's none...!

26:30.790 --> 26:34.060
It's none of your business,
all right?

26:44.871 --> 26:47.039
You're driving

26:47.073 --> 26:48.307
too close to them.

26:48.340 --> 26:50.810
What are you trying
to do, the PIT maneuver?

26:50.843 --> 26:52.411
(siren blips)

26:52.444 --> 26:54.814
Look in your rearview mirror.

26:54.847 --> 26:56.749
See the dope they
just threw

26:56.783 --> 26:58.117
out of the car?

26:59.451 --> 27:01.688
If you weren't so far
up their ass,

27:01.721 --> 27:03.723
you'd have seen that.

27:08.695 --> 27:10.697
Go get the dope.

27:13.766 --> 27:17.336
(over P.A.):
Driver, put your hands outside
the car where I can see them.

27:17.369 --> 27:19.739
Passenger!

27:19.772 --> 27:22.408
Put your hands outside of the
vehicle where I can see them.

27:22.441 --> 27:26.412
COMMUNICATIONS (over radio):
U-3, report back
to 2622 South Ardmore.

27:26.445 --> 27:28.748
See the mother
of the missing child.

27:28.781 --> 27:31.117
U-3. Roger that.

27:34.787 --> 27:37.724
Ma'am, please
come over here,

27:37.724 --> 27:41.093
kneel down, and lay flat
on your stomach.

27:41.127 --> 27:42.929
I can't.
CHICKIE:
Ma'am?

27:42.962 --> 27:45.164
I'm pregnant.

27:45.197 --> 27:46.833
Keep your eyes on her.

27:46.866 --> 27:48.300
Control her.

27:48.334 --> 27:49.769
Don't look at me!

27:51.470 --> 27:54.106
Ma'am, come over here.

27:55.875 --> 27:57.744
Felony kneeling.

27:57.744 --> 27:59.812
Kneel down,
put your hands above your head.

27:59.846 --> 28:01.047
Now!

28:01.080 --> 28:02.314
Do it!

28:02.348 --> 28:03.816
(clears throat)

28:03.850 --> 28:05.785
Hands above your head!

28:05.818 --> 28:07.854
(woman grunts)

28:11.490 --> 28:13.259
(quietly):
No frigging command presence.

28:15.327 --> 28:16.796
(sighs)

28:16.829 --> 28:19.365
She said you
had kind eyes.

28:19.398 --> 28:21.333
(speaking Korean)

28:24.771 --> 28:27.373
She wants to show you something
in the house.

28:27.406 --> 28:29.341
(speaking Korean)

28:47.860 --> 28:49.796
(speaking Korean)

28:53.399 --> 28:56.235
Yeah? Uh, ask her if
they've ever taken Jane there.

28:56.268 --> 28:58.370
(speaking Korean)

29:00.339 --> 29:02.141
JASON:
Never.

29:24.430 --> 29:26.999
Jane!

29:27.033 --> 29:28.134
Jane?!

29:30.469 --> 29:33.372
Jane?!
WOMAN:
Hey!

29:33.405 --> 29:34.573
What...?

29:34.606 --> 29:37.209
I'm sorry.

29:37.243 --> 29:39.311
I'm sorry; I'm looking
for somebody; I'm sorry.

29:46.218 --> 29:48.988
Yo! Yo, excuse me.

29:49.021 --> 29:50.857
Great. Thanks.

29:50.857 --> 29:52.992
I'm looking for a little girl,
nine years old, Korean.

29:53.025 --> 29:54.226
You see anything
like that?

29:54.260 --> 29:56.896
Uh, what kind of
car was she driving?

29:56.929 --> 30:00.232
Look, if I had seen a little
girl walking by herself,

30:00.266 --> 30:02.969
don't think I'd
turn her in?

30:03.002 --> 30:04.103
Try the west garage.

30:04.136 --> 30:05.471
Um, got a card?

30:05.504 --> 30:07.439
Yeah.

30:09.141 --> 30:12.078
Okay. Give you a call
if she turns up.

30:16.115 --> 30:17.850
What are you doing?

30:17.884 --> 30:18.851
I'm writing.

30:20.119 --> 30:21.087
What are you writing?

30:22.121 --> 30:23.555
My blog.

30:23.589 --> 30:26.192
Thought you were gonna
give that up.

30:26.225 --> 30:27.493
No.

30:27.526 --> 30:30.362
Why would I stop
blogging about my life?

30:30.396 --> 30:33.499
Did you write
about me getting shot?

30:33.532 --> 30:35.467
Yes.

30:38.037 --> 30:39.438
It happened to me,
too, Russell.

30:39.471 --> 30:40.572
Oh, did it, Dina?

30:40.606 --> 30:42.274
(scoffing laugh)

30:42.308 --> 30:43.910
'Cause I don't see you
lying in bed

30:43.943 --> 30:45.477
with a piss bag
and tubes coming out of you.

30:45.511 --> 30:47.079
I don't see you having
your intestines carved out.

30:47.113 --> 30:48.647
I don't see you
limping around here...

30:48.680 --> 30:50.049
WOMAN: You got time.
Visiting hours are
still another hour.

30:50.082 --> 30:51.517
Come on in.

30:51.550 --> 30:53.285
...you're probably never gonna
get to do again!

30:55.187 --> 30:58.157
It's not a good time.

30:58.190 --> 31:01.327
Um, yeah. I'm sorry.

31:08.367 --> 31:10.069
...'cause she's obsessed
with the Nokia Center.

31:10.102 --> 31:11.503
She does drawings,
paintings.

31:11.537 --> 31:13.672
I don't know.
She's...

31:13.705 --> 31:16.442
Is there any way people
can get back up in here?

31:28.320 --> 31:29.655
You got
any other monitors?

31:29.688 --> 31:31.023
Mm-mm.

31:31.057 --> 31:32.091
Any other angles, anything?

31:32.124 --> 31:33.592
(Ben sighs)

31:33.625 --> 31:34.961
All right.

31:49.708 --> 31:51.677
Are you Jane?

31:51.710 --> 31:54.513
The stage measures
14,000 square feet.

31:54.546 --> 31:58.284
No seat is further than
220 feet from the stage.

31:58.317 --> 32:02.054
Orchestra has 4,340 seats.

32:02.088 --> 32:05.124
The seats are
23 1/2 inches wide.

32:05.157 --> 32:07.259
That's great.

32:07.293 --> 32:09.595
Great.

32:09.628 --> 32:12.698
Okay. Come on.

32:16.235 --> 32:17.369
BEN:
It's not a problem.

32:17.403 --> 32:18.570
MOTHER:
Thank you. Thank you.

32:18.604 --> 32:20.139
You're welcome.
You're welcome.

32:20.172 --> 32:22.408
You just make sure
you get her some help.

32:22.441 --> 32:24.576
Okay? Make sure you
get her help? Yeah?

32:25.444 --> 32:26.545
It's okay.

32:26.578 --> 32:27.713
No problem.
No problem.

32:27.746 --> 32:29.615
(phone ringing)

32:29.648 --> 32:31.150
Sherman.

32:31.183 --> 32:32.551
STELLA (on phone):
Ben, it's Stella.

32:32.584 --> 32:34.086
I think he's here.

32:34.120 --> 32:36.055
I keep hearing things
outside my doorway

32:36.088 --> 32:37.256
and I think he's got a key.

32:37.289 --> 32:39.358
All right.
Hang up and call 911.

32:39.391 --> 32:41.193
Do it now, Stella!

32:41.227 --> 32:44.530
See, the thing
with police work?

32:44.563 --> 32:46.298
It's a perishable skill.

32:46.332 --> 32:50.502
You know, you don't
use it, you lose it.

32:54.040 --> 32:58.077
Maybe you're not cut out
for the street anymore.

32:58.110 --> 33:02.548
Then you can go over to the
communications division.

33:02.581 --> 33:05.384
Just... shut up.

33:05.417 --> 33:08.187
Okay?

33:10.456 --> 33:12.424
You want to take a gun
off the street?

33:20.266 --> 33:22.134
Sir. Stop.

33:22.168 --> 33:23.435
Turn around.

33:23.469 --> 33:26.105
Put your hands
in the air.

33:26.138 --> 33:28.207
Turn around.
Put your hands in the air.

33:30.409 --> 33:33.112
Interlace your fingers
behind your head.

33:33.145 --> 33:35.081
Spread your legs.

33:37.216 --> 33:39.151
(siren approaches)

33:55.201 --> 33:56.602
How'd you know
he had a gun?

33:56.635 --> 33:59.171
I have cop eyes,
just the same as you.

34:14.220 --> 34:15.454
You missed this one.

34:26.598 --> 34:30.136
(siren wailing)

34:55.927 --> 34:57.829
(grunts)

35:02.301 --> 35:04.636
(sirens approach)

35:06.238 --> 35:07.639
Breathe!

35:07.673 --> 35:10.242
Breathe!
Breathe!

35:10.276 --> 35:11.743
Come on, breathe!
Breathe!

35:11.777 --> 35:13.645
Sherm! Sherm,
we got this!
Breathe!

35:13.679 --> 35:15.247
We got it!

35:15.281 --> 35:17.849
(panting)

35:17.883 --> 35:21.287
Do something!
Help her!

35:21.320 --> 35:25.691
OFFICER:
Control 118-16 to 1097.
We're code four on that 242.

35:25.724 --> 35:28.594
Be advised. Victim is
nonresponsive at this time.

35:31.630 --> 35:34.666
(shouts)

35:34.700 --> 35:36.668
(enraged yelling)

35:36.702 --> 35:39.405
(panting)

35:43.975 --> 35:45.211
(angry grunt)

35:49.848 --> 35:52.251
(lock buzzes)

35:52.284 --> 35:54.220
(door thuds open)

36:14.005 --> 36:15.607
You okay?

36:15.641 --> 36:17.643
Fine.

36:25.517 --> 36:27.819
Everybody's congratulating me
like I did something great.

36:27.853 --> 36:29.788
I hit that guy, hard.

36:31.957 --> 36:33.892
He had cuffs on.

36:36.995 --> 36:38.930
I don't know
where the lines are.

36:43.935 --> 36:46.438
You got a lot of
power out there.

36:48.540 --> 36:50.809
You can't get control of it,
maybe you shouldn't be here.

36:52.911 --> 36:55.847
Look, everyone, when
they get out of the academy,

36:55.881 --> 36:57.449
thinks it's all
black and white.

36:57.483 --> 36:59.285
But you know what?
It isn't.

37:03.489 --> 37:05.424
We live in the gray.

37:08.527 --> 37:10.462
We live there.

37:13.532 --> 37:15.401
Now you know what
you're capable of.

37:38.023 --> 37:39.858
That's it!

37:39.891 --> 37:42.961
Huh? Who...?

37:42.994 --> 37:44.430
You?

37:44.463 --> 37:46.465
How could you
do this to me?

37:46.498 --> 37:47.899
You deserved it.

37:47.933 --> 37:52.070
Coming in here
with your fancy pictures,

37:52.103 --> 37:54.039
thinking you're
all that.

38:00.746 --> 38:03.515
Hey, I'm sorry
about before.

38:03.549 --> 38:06.485
No, it's all right.
I...

38:06.518 --> 38:09.020
I should have kept
my big mouth shut.

38:09.054 --> 38:11.757
Like you said,
none of my damn business.

38:11.790 --> 38:15.361
No, I think
you're right.

38:15.361 --> 38:16.828
(sighs)

38:16.862 --> 38:18.564
I need to give
him his space.

38:21.533 --> 38:22.868
I woke up today

38:22.901 --> 38:24.503
'cause I had a
dream about him.

38:24.536 --> 38:27.373
I was in the shoot-out,

38:27.373 --> 38:29.375
but I wasn't
shooting Marta's kid.

38:29.375 --> 38:30.976
I was...

38:31.009 --> 38:32.944
shooting Russell.

38:34.079 --> 38:36.047
It just... I don't know.

38:36.081 --> 38:38.016
It just stuck
with me all day.

38:40.386 --> 38:43.088
It must be hard.

38:43.121 --> 38:45.090
Knowing how much
he loved it.

38:45.123 --> 38:47.859
Not knowing
if he'll make it back.

38:50.095 --> 38:53.965
Survivor's guilt
or whatever they call it.

38:55.467 --> 38:57.436
You know what?

38:57.469 --> 38:59.538
Let's go get a drink.

38:59.571 --> 39:00.672
Yes.

39:00.706 --> 39:02.408
Yes, okay.
Let's go.

39:02.408 --> 39:03.542
Oh, w-where?

39:03.575 --> 39:05.143
Where?

39:05.176 --> 39:07.913
Yeah, Hollywood,
you're so slick.

39:07.946 --> 39:10.115
I don't want to end
up on Sunset Strip

39:10.148 --> 39:13.985
with a bunch of teenagers
drinking fancy $20 martinis.

39:14.019 --> 39:15.754
Did you just call me
Hollywood?

39:15.787 --> 39:17.456
I did.

39:17.489 --> 39:19.425
Hollywood?

39:19.458 --> 39:20.559
* Hollywood.

39:20.592 --> 39:22.694
You do know
I'm from the Bronx?

39:22.728 --> 39:24.430
(siren wailing in distance)

39:24.430 --> 39:26.432
(dog barking in distance)

39:53.959 --> 39:55.894
(sniffs)

40:03.001 --> 40:04.936
Thanks for coming.

40:11.943 --> 40:14.145
I once had to do
CPR on a baby.

40:16.247 --> 40:21.487
Was eight...
nine months old.

40:23.555 --> 40:27.225
(grunts)

40:27.258 --> 40:31.763
She had choked on
a piece of apple.

40:32.864 --> 40:34.833
(sighs)

40:34.866 --> 40:39.805
By the time I got there,
she was dead, but, uh...

40:39.838 --> 40:41.773
I couldn't stop.

40:44.843 --> 40:47.546
I'd give her two breaths,
compressed her chest,

40:47.579 --> 40:49.147
two more breaths,
compressed again,

40:49.180 --> 40:52.083
just over
and over and over.

40:53.184 --> 40:56.254
(sighs deeply)

40:56.287 --> 40:58.824
I dreamt about her
for a long time after that.

41:00.692 --> 41:02.027
A couple years.

41:04.863 --> 41:07.533
(sighs)

41:09.234 --> 41:11.637
Once in a while,
I still dream about her.

41:15.641 --> 41:17.643
That I save her.

41:22.648 --> 41:25.551
You can't save
everyone.

41:38.296 --> 41:40.966
Owes me a favor.

41:40.999 --> 41:43.935
(lift whirring)
